# MyCobot cuRobo project rules

- Read `@spec.md` before changing architecture, planning behavior, frame conventions, configuration, or safety logic.
- Implement one specification phase at a time and satisfy its acceptance criteria before starting the next phase.
- Keep the core `mycobot_curobo` package independent of ROS 2, Isaac Sim, Isaac Lab, physical MyCobot drivers, sensors, and RL frameworks. Host-side Isaac scaffolding under `isaac_sim/` and `scripts/host/` is allowed for Phase 7+ but must not become a Phase 0–6 runtime dependency.
- Follow `docs/implementation_phases.md` for the Phase 0–10 roadmap (Isaac Sim, residual RL, hardware).
- Use typed domain objects instead of unstructured dictionaries across core module boundaries.
- Keep units explicit: meters, radians, seconds, and scalar-first `wxyz` quaternions.
- Never infer frame names, joint order, units, or TCP calibration silently.
- Expected planning infeasibility returns a structured result. Invalid environment or configuration raises a specific error.
- Do not mark a plan executable until independent validation passes.
- Do not issue commands to physical hardware in this project phase.
- Add tests for every behavior change. Keep random tests reproducible with explicit seeds.
- Do not suppress errors, weaken thresholds, or skip tests merely to obtain a passing run.
- Develop each numbered phase on `wip_phaseN`. Do not add Phase N+1 work to
  `wip_phaseN`.
- After a phase passes all applicable gates, commit and push `wip_phaseN`,
  rebase it onto the latest `origin/main`, re-run affected gates, and update
  the published phase branch if needed. Then fast-forward `main` to the same
  tested commit and push `main`; do not merge `main` into a phase branch.
- Preserve completed `wip_phaseN` branches as historical phase snapshots.
- Update `spec.md`, `README.md`, `REFERENCES.md`, `STATUS.md`, `CHANGES.md`,
  `docs/last_prompt.md`, and the applicable phase report before landing each
  phase. Do not edit those landing documents again after the final phase push
  in the same phase.
